source_url: http://www.cms.int/news/PRESS/nwPR2008/03_Mar/nw_120308_Dakar.htm -- Under the chairmanship of Senegal, the meeting adopted an amendment of the MoU text permitting the establishment of an Advisory Committee, the official adoption of the Coordination Unit already operating and specific encouragement for important range states to join the MoU. The last point invites concerned countries to join and add value to this key agreement for turtle conservation, which CMS and stakeholders have managed to revitalize over the last three years. Amendments were agreed and range states were requested to comment on the text and inform the CMS Secretariat accordingly by 21 March 2008. --
